00:38:48,126 --> 00:38:49,828
but we had found our road,

748
00:38:49,895 --> 00:38:52,063
and that's all that mattered.

749
00:38:53,164 --> 00:38:54,533
Oh, yes!

750
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,668
That's the best thing
I've ever seen!

751
00:38:56,735 --> 00:39:00,406
Yes,
it is the road to freedom!

752
00:39:00,472 --> 00:39:02,841
- (HISSING)
- What the hell was that?

753
00:39:05,310 --> 00:39:09,314
Something has just exploded
at the back of my car.

754
00:39:09,415 --> 00:39:11,617
Oh, dear.

755
00:39:11,683 --> 00:39:14,052
By the time my colleagues
had got back to me,

756
00:39:14,119 --> 00:39:16,922
I'd worked out
what the problem was.

757
00:39:16,988 --> 00:39:19,157
It's really
straightforward, OK?

758
00:39:19,224 --> 00:39:22,661
- The top bolt has come
out of the shock absorber.
- Right.

759
00:39:22,728 --> 00:39:26,264
It shot up, boinged
into the coolant pipe,

760
00:39:26,331 --> 00:39:29,668
and three gallons of water
have simply burst out,

761
00:39:29,735 --> 00:39:32,471
going everywhere
except into the engine.

762
00:39:32,538 --> 00:39:36,274
- Right.
- So all I've got to do
is reattach the top bolt...

763
00:39:36,341 --> 00:39:40,846
mend the pipe and find
three gallons of water...

764
00:39:40,912 --> 00:39:45,250
which I shall get
from a passing motorist,
and I'll be on my way.

765
00:39:45,316 --> 00:39:46,351
Right.

766
00:39:46,452 --> 00:39:47,586
All I could do
with a hand with

767
00:39:47,653 --> 00:39:49,154
is just lifting the car up

768
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:51,289
so I can reattach the, um...

769
00:39:51,356 --> 00:39:53,224
Yeah. Well,
is there anybody here?

770
00:39:53,291 --> 00:39:55,894
- There's...
- I suppose a motorist
will pass eventually.

771
00:39:55,961 --> 00:39:58,630
The one that gives you water
will also lift it up for you.

772
00:39:58,697 --> 00:40:00,466
You could just
lift it up a little bit.

773
00:40:00,466 --> 00:40:02,400
Or we could go
and have a beer.

774
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:02,468
Or we could go
and have a beer.
- I hear traffic.
- Yes.
- We'd better not be here.

775
00:40:02,468 --> 00:40:04,335
- I hear traffic.
- Yes.
- We'd better not be here.

776
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:06,438
We don't want to interfere
when you're trying to talk

777
00:40:06,505 --> 00:40:08,006
'cause we might put them off.

778
00:40:08,073 --> 00:40:13,211
(ENGINES REV)

779
00:40:13,278 --> 00:40:14,613
Right.

780
00:40:25,524 --> 00:40:29,795
Somewhere along here
there will be a place,

781
00:40:29,861 --> 00:40:32,964
and that place
will have a bar in it

782
00:40:33,031 --> 00:40:34,566
that will contain beer.

783
00:40:39,237 --> 00:40:40,506
Do you have any water?

784
00:40:40,572 --> 00:40:41,940
- Huh?
- Water.

785
00:40:42,007 --> 00:40:44,242
Because the radiator
has blown,

786
00:40:44,309 --> 00:40:45,911
so I need just three gallons.

787
00:40:45,977 --> 00:40:49,214
Look, you've got some water
there. Just a bucket.

788
00:40:52,751 --> 00:40:55,621
It's an actual water lorry...

789
00:40:55,687 --> 00:40:58,490
leaking water,
and he won't give me any.

790
00:41:02,961 --> 00:41:05,230
Eventually,
I flagged down a local

791
00:41:05,296 --> 00:41:07,533
who had water to spare.

792
00:41:07,533 --> 00:41:09,568
Thank you.

793
00:41:09,635 --> 00:41:12,003
And then I got on
with the repairs.

794
00:41:12,070 --> 00:41:16,642
That is one reassembled
shock absorber.

795
00:41:16,708 --> 00:41:18,143
That's reattached,

796
00:41:18,209 --> 00:41:20,879
so that's the cooling system
back in one piece.

797
00:41:25,116 --> 00:41:28,754
JAMES: After an exhausting
five-hour drive,

798
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:31,322
Richard and I finally
reached a town,

799
00:41:31,389 --> 00:41:35,761
which turned out to be
Namibia's capital city:
Windhoek,

800
00:41:35,827 --> 00:41:38,830
and we too were
taking on liquids.

801
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,715
Mm.

802
00:42:03,021 --> 00:42:03,989
