809
00:42:20,271 --> 00:42:21,607
Bled that,

810
00:42:21,607 --> 00:42:23,341
bled all the stuff
going into the engine.

811
00:42:23,408 --> 00:42:24,509
This is the header pipe.

812
00:42:24,610 --> 00:42:26,311
Everything is bled, and yet,

813
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,814
you do a mile, it overheats.

814
00:42:28,880 --> 00:42:30,616
Another mile, overheats.

815
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:46,331
Well, we've covered...
20 miles in four hours.

816
00:42:52,638 --> 00:42:53,872
(SIGHS)

817
00:43:01,246 --> 00:43:06,384
This is the sixth time
in 30 miles that's happened.

818
00:43:06,451 --> 00:43:09,387
Whilst my colleagues
embraced beer and bed,

819
00:43:09,454 --> 00:43:13,124
I steeled myself
for the longest, coldest,

820
00:43:13,191 --> 00:43:17,062
most frustrating night
of my life.

821
00:43:17,128 --> 00:43:19,064
(HISSING)

822
00:43:22,668 --> 00:43:24,169
JEREMY:
The roads are getting worse.

823
00:43:24,235 --> 00:43:26,672
Honestly, my bones
are going to shatter.

824
00:43:26,705 --> 00:43:29,741
- (ENGINE REVS)
- Oh, my God!

825
00:43:29,808 --> 00:43:31,109
(SCREAMS)

826
00:43:34,980 --> 00:43:38,784
- I've had a great idea.
